wikipedia_page.main: Yusuf Ssozi (born  (1981-12-20) 20 December 1981) is a Ugandan-British former professional rugby league footballer who played in the 2000s. He played at club level in the Super League for the London Broncos (Heritage No. 374) (2000-2001), the Batley Bulldogs, the York City Knights, Gateshead Thunder, Doncaster (Heritage No. 931) (2006), in National League One for the Sheffield Eagles (2007), and the Bradford Bulls, as a prop.
